1
00:00:06,020 --> 00:00:07,390
[All of Her]

2
00:00:07,420 --> 00:00:10,240
[Episode 4]

3
00:00:10,260 --> 00:00:18,360
[First encounter]

4
00:00:23,559 --> 00:00:24,200
Sorry.

5
00:00:24,559 --> 00:00:25,520
You look so beautiful

6
00:00:26,079 --> 00:00:27,479
when you're under the tree.

7
00:00:27,879 --> 00:00:28,920
So I took a photo.

8
00:00:33,959 --> 00:00:34,560
What do you think?

9
00:00:35,639 --> 00:00:36,319
Nice.

10
00:00:38,599 --> 00:00:38,919
Well...

11
00:00:39,360 --> 00:00:40,919
Can I exchange this with you?

12
00:00:48,119 --> 00:00:49,240
(What taste is this?)

13
00:00:49,959 --> 00:00:50,880
(Ginger soda?)

14
00:00:57,680 --> 00:00:58,240
Ze'an.

15
00:00:58,599 --> 00:00:59,479
Thank you.

16
00:01:04,639 --> 00:01:05,319
Can I have something else?

17
00:01:06,319 --> 00:01:07,000
What a coincidence.

18
00:01:07,319 --> 00:01:08,839
Your brother also doesn't like this.

19
00:01:10,199 --> 00:01:11,279
I doubt

20
00:01:11,559 --> 00:01:12,919
many people like this flavor.

21
00:01:13,559 --> 00:01:14,760
I'm sorry.

22
00:01:15,199 --> 00:01:16,239
I only have this here.

23
00:01:34,959 --> 00:01:36,160
Similar preference

24
00:01:36,680 --> 00:01:37,760
doesn't mean anything.

25
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:42,680
I'm not Zejia.

26
00:01:42,959 --> 00:01:43,919
Stop testing me.

27
00:01:45,839 --> 00:01:46,519
You're right.

28
00:01:47,760 --> 00:01:48,599
I think

29
00:01:48,879 --> 00:01:50,519
I should move on now.

30
00:01:52,599 --> 00:01:53,319
What about you?

31
00:01:53,760 --> 00:01:55,319
What do you think about my offer?

32
00:01:56,959 --> 00:01:58,120
Like I said.

33
00:01:58,879 --> 00:01:59,800
What benefits do I get?

34
00:02:00,919 --> 00:02:03,160
You don't drink, sleep around,

35
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:04,800
gamble, or act recklessly.

36
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:06,879
Raise any condition you like.

37
00:02:07,839 --> 00:02:09,039
Well.

38
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:11,679
I want you to promise me one thing.

39
00:02:12,880 --> 00:02:14,160
But I'll let you know what it is

40
00:02:14,440 --> 00:02:15,679
after I think of it.

41
00:02:17,440 --> 00:02:18,039
Fine.

42
00:02:18,720 --> 00:02:19,360
Deal.

43
00:02:42,919 --> 00:02:44,080
I've connected the cameras

44
00:02:44,559 --> 00:02:45,720
when I was scanning her room.

45
00:02:46,039 --> 00:02:47,759
You're cunning.

46
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:49,559
If Yan Zhen finds this out,

47
00:02:49,559 --> 00:02:50,399
she might kick you out.

48
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:51,679
I'm doing this for her goodness.

49
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:52,399
Hurry.

50
00:02:57,880 --> 00:02:58,639
Done.

51
00:02:58,839 --> 00:03:00,639
Should I install
the security identification system?

52
00:03:01,759 --> 00:03:02,240
I'll do it.

53
00:03:07,679 --> 00:03:08,960
How about the security guards?

54
00:03:09,479 --> 00:03:10,679
To avoid any suspicions,

55
00:03:10,880 --> 00:03:12,479
only one is left, as per the rules.

56
00:03:12,720 --> 00:03:14,440
Go up from the stairwell
on the first level.

57
00:03:14,679 --> 00:03:16,800
I'm heading to the control room
to cover for you.

58
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:18,918
[Anshi Group]
Ms. Yan.

59
00:03:18,919 --> 00:03:19,360
Good job.

60
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:22,199
I'm inside.

61
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:37,119
Mr. Gu.

62
00:03:37,479 --> 00:03:38,039
Mr. Liu.

63
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:40,479
Quite a few people

64
00:03:40,679 --> 00:03:41,800
working late these days.

65
00:03:42,279 --> 00:03:43,199
We run out of manpower.

66
00:03:43,639 --> 00:03:44,720
Be careful not to make any mistakes.

67
00:03:45,039 --> 00:03:45,679
Yes.

68
00:03:53,220 --> 00:03:59,120
[Anshi Group]

69
00:04:00,919 --> 00:04:02,160
(When you enter the file room,)

70
00:04:02,559 --> 00:04:03,759
(you only have ten minutes.)

71
00:04:04,520 --> 00:04:05,600
(When ten minutes are up,)

72
00:04:05,679 --> 00:04:06,679
(you must leave immediately,)

73
00:04:06,919 --> 00:04:08,199
(no matter whether you find it or not.)

74
00:04:23,440 --> 00:04:23,920
What's wrong?

75
00:04:24,959 --> 00:04:26,839
I saw Ms. Yan's car in the parking lot.

76
00:04:30,660 --> 00:04:32,480
[GPS tracking]

77
00:04:32,760 --> 00:04:33,279
All right.

78
00:04:41,239 --> 00:04:42,679
No wonder

79
00:04:42,679 --> 00:04:44,079
she insisted on keeping me there
as a bodyguard.

80
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:47,320
Turns out she aimed at my access card.

81
00:04:49,500 --> 00:04:50,740
[Ledgers]

82
00:04:58,150 --> 00:04:59,800
[Chu Ze'an]

83
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:06,239
Mr. Gu.

84
00:05:06,399 --> 00:05:07,720
I'll take another round downstairs.

85
00:05:09,359 --> 00:05:10,079
Go on.

86
00:05:13,820 --> 00:05:15,580
[Gu Cheng: Someone's here. Leave.]

87
00:05:58,560 --> 00:06:02,170
♪Waiting for the wilted flower
to finally fall silent♪

88
00:06:02,370 --> 00:06:05,950
♪Waiting for the time
divides the sunset glow♪

89
00:06:06,150 --> 00:06:08,860
♪He stalks my mind and memories♪

90
00:06:08,880 --> 00:06:09,799
You...

91
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:10,959
Don't remember me?

92
00:06:10,980 --> 00:06:12,710
♪Struggling in this perpetual cycle♪

93
00:06:13,920 --> 00:06:14,720
Under the tree.

94
00:06:16,519 --> 00:06:17,239
Polaroid.

95
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:19,920
Ginger soda.

96
00:06:21,380 --> 00:06:24,920
♪Tick, tock, tick, tock♪

97
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:26,519
What are you doing in the file room?

98
00:06:26,540 --> 00:06:27,900
♪Tears are speaking♪

99
00:06:29,480 --> 00:06:30,720
I'm looking for documents.

100
00:06:32,079 --> 00:06:32,679
Me too.

101
00:06:34,239 --> 00:06:35,559
If so,

102
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:38,279
this is just between us.

103
00:06:40,440 --> 00:06:43,370
♪Or just let it go?♪

104
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:53,239
Zhen.

105
00:06:53,640 --> 00:06:54,920
Is it thrilling to be a thief?

106
00:06:55,359 --> 00:06:56,920
Why haven't you rested up yet?

107
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:59,519
I couldn't sleep, so I took a stroll.

108
00:06:59,559 --> 00:07:00,640
And you ended up coming here?

109
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:02,119
Why are you here, then?

110
00:07:05,799 --> 00:07:07,799
I'm here to get my card back.

111
00:07:22,320 --> 00:07:22,920
Why?

112
00:07:23,679 --> 00:07:24,799
Afraid of being bugged?

113
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:28,559
You requested me to be your bodyguard.

114
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:30,679
Could you please inform me in advance

115
00:07:30,679 --> 00:07:31,799
before you come out

116
00:07:32,359 --> 00:07:33,799
for an adventure?

117
00:07:34,760 --> 00:07:36,279
You made me look unprofessional.

118
00:07:37,320 --> 00:07:37,799
All right.

119
00:07:38,600 --> 00:07:39,519
I'll inform you next time.

120
00:07:40,519 --> 00:07:41,200
No more next time.

121
00:07:41,839 --> 00:07:42,760
Now tell me.

122
00:07:43,160 --> 00:07:44,920
Why did you take the fake ledgers
from the file room?

123
00:07:46,679 --> 00:07:47,399
Fake?

124
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:48,679
Yes.

125
00:07:49,079 --> 00:07:49,480
How did you...

126
00:07:49,480 --> 00:07:51,359
My brother took the real copy

127
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:55,480
during the audit four years ago.

128
00:07:57,959 --> 00:07:59,320
But you were overseas back then.

129
00:08:00,239 --> 00:08:01,440
How do you know

130
00:08:02,559 --> 00:08:03,600
when I'm clueless about this?

131
00:08:08,760 --> 00:08:09,799
Perhaps

132
00:08:11,640 --> 00:08:13,040
he didn't want you to get hurt.

133
00:08:13,440 --> 00:08:14,519
After all, he ran into big trouble

134
00:08:14,640 --> 00:08:16,640
when he was auditing this.

135
00:08:17,040 --> 00:08:18,119
Even so, do you still want to try?

136
00:08:19,799 --> 00:08:21,440
In the worst-case scenario,
I may meet him six feet under.

137
00:08:27,190 --> 00:08:30,100
[Detailed Account of Income and Expense]

138
00:08:33,039 --> 00:08:34,599
Is the real ledger with you?

139
00:08:37,799 --> 00:08:38,599
Of course not.

140
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:42,200
The situation is still unclear.

141
00:08:42,799 --> 00:08:44,400
Don't trust people around you.

142
00:08:44,640 --> 00:08:45,359
Gu Cheng...

143
00:08:45,359 --> 00:08:46,520
None of your business.

144
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:52,359
You're a good guy.

145
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:55,719
I am.

146
00:08:58,919 --> 00:09:00,000
Let's go, bodyguard.

147
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:02,840
Where to?

148
00:09:04,119 --> 00:09:05,239
Get in the car first.

149
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:41,880
I know what you mean to do.

150
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:45,239
My brother has an allergy to alcohol.

151
00:09:56,280 --> 00:09:56,960
But

152
00:09:57,440 --> 00:09:58,280
I'm not him.

153
00:10:26,640 --> 00:10:28,000
Are you a good drinker?

154
00:10:28,599 --> 00:10:30,159
I forget him when I'm drunk.

155
00:10:30,719 --> 00:10:32,440
What do you think?

156
00:11:05,799 --> 00:11:07,119
I want one...

157
00:11:07,479 --> 00:11:08,520
One shot.

158
00:11:09,119 --> 00:11:09,880
You've drunk too much.

159
00:11:12,760 --> 00:11:13,760
Zejia.

160
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:14,799
Let's go home.

161
00:11:51,590 --> 00:11:54,530
♪Once again, I'm crazy for you♪

162
00:11:54,760 --> 00:11:56,810
♪Just like before♪

163
00:11:59,570 --> 00:12:03,380
♪Having a sleepless night like a fool♪

164
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:04,200
Zejia.

165
00:12:05,039 --> 00:12:05,760
Don't go.

166
00:12:06,050 --> 00:12:11,700
♪Silence replaces the promise,
then turns into a fib♪

167
00:12:14,930 --> 00:12:18,980
♪I leave to set you free♪

168
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:19,520
What did you say?

169
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:20,880
Zejia.

170
00:12:21,479 --> 00:12:22,840
You're back.

171
00:12:22,860 --> 00:12:24,480
♪Once again, I cry and laugh for you♪

172
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:26,080
No.

173
00:12:26,840 --> 00:12:27,760
I'm not him.

174
00:12:28,320 --> 00:12:29,200
You are.

175
00:12:29,799 --> 00:12:30,559
You're him.

176
00:12:30,580 --> 00:12:33,890
♪It's been a while,
but I can't say it out♪

177
00:12:33,919 --> 00:12:34,599
Stop pretending.

178
00:12:35,559 --> 00:12:36,559
I know you're not drunk.

179
00:12:36,580 --> 00:12:38,920
♪Once again, my heart breaks
in drunkenness for you♪

180
00:12:39,380 --> 00:12:42,290
♪I remain stubborn♪

181
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:48,790
♪Ever since I have left you♪

182
00:12:52,599 --> 00:12:53,599
You can tell?

183
00:12:55,880 --> 00:12:56,919
Zejia told me

184
00:12:57,679 --> 00:12:58,799
that you cry when you're drunk.

185
00:13:04,599 --> 00:13:05,280
To think

186
00:13:06,440 --> 00:13:08,200
you miss him so much.

187
00:13:11,920 --> 00:13:16,250
♪Who will cherish it,
who will waste it?♪

188
00:13:18,560 --> 00:13:23,490
♪Who truly cares
if it is an accident or being forced?♪

189
00:13:24,719 --> 00:13:25,599
I'll repeat this again.

190
00:13:26,039 --> 00:13:26,840
I'm no one else but me.

191
00:13:28,479 --> 00:13:29,239
I don't believe it.

192
00:13:33,950 --> 00:13:38,960
♪Every moment since your departure♪

193
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:43,150
♪I become weak♪

194
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:46,380
♪And insincere♪

195
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:47,239
If so,

196
00:13:47,960 --> 00:13:49,200
let's be frank with each other.

197
00:13:54,850 --> 00:14:00,780
♪I look terrible and fall from grace♪

198
00:14:02,039 --> 00:14:02,919
You should go now.

199
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:04,880
I'm going to bed.

200
00:14:06,510 --> 00:14:07,480
♪With one more sight of you♪

201
00:14:07,500 --> 00:14:08,680
♪Love deepens again♪

202
00:14:09,010 --> 00:14:11,500
♪Just like before♪

203
00:14:14,230 --> 00:14:18,610
♪Having a sleepless night like a fool♪

204
00:14:20,630 --> 00:14:21,560
♪Tears break out again♪

205
00:14:21,770 --> 00:14:23,040
♪My heart is in pieces♪

206
00:14:23,260 --> 00:14:25,980
♪Just like before♪

207
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:29,039
Good night.

208
00:14:56,960 --> 00:14:57,719
Good night.

209
00:15:13,960 --> 00:15:17,570
♪Waiting for the wilted flower
to finally fall silent♪

210
00:15:17,770 --> 00:15:21,480
♪Waiting for the time
divides the sunset glow♪

211
00:15:21,550 --> 00:15:25,320
♪He stalks my mind and memories♪

212
00:15:25,380 --> 00:15:28,310
♪Struggling in this perpetual cycle♪

213
00:15:29,020 --> 00:15:32,730
♪Promises are answering his lies♪

214
00:15:32,890 --> 00:15:36,760
♪I'm just a walker-on
in this tear-jerker♪

215
00:15:36,780 --> 00:15:40,390
♪Tick, tock, tick, tock♪

216
00:15:40,550 --> 00:15:43,630
♪Tears are speaking♪

217
00:15:44,480 --> 00:15:47,980
♪Mist blinds his eyes
from seeing rose graffiti♪

218
00:15:48,100 --> 00:15:51,970
♪The dialogue sounds hoarse,
I can only hide my words within♪

219
00:15:51,990 --> 00:15:55,820
♪Love me, will you? Quiet, silly♪

220
00:15:55,920 --> 00:15:59,120
♪Or just let it go?♪

221
00:16:01,452 --> 00:16:03,829
[Grief is a sneaky thing,
always coming and going like some guest]

222
00:16:03,830 --> 00:16:06,206
[you didn't invite and can't turn away.
Kristin Hannah.]
